A 30-year old Alshabaab suspect has been shot dead in Kwale County. The suspected terrorist was gunned down by security agencies on Friday. The incident was announced by the Directorate of Criminal Investigations (DCI) through its official Twitter account. DCI stated that the suspect who was not immediately identified was killed at Ngomeni area by a multi-agency team acting on a tip-off from members of the public. “A 30 year-old al Shabaab suspect was shot dead today in #Ngombeni area, Kwale County by a Multi-Agency Team acting on a tip-off from the public,” reads the tweet in part. The DCI divulged that a police corporal was injured during the shootout and is undergoing treatment at an undisclosed health facility. “A loaded Glock Pistol and IED making materials were recovered,” DCI stated.